howto:
h1. RMI Example
h2. Summary
This example shows how to implement a remote method invocation mechanism. The technique uses a LinkedBlockingQueue, and a Proxy to call methods on a remote node.
h2. How to run
*Node 1:* {code} $ javac *.java $ start-tc-server & $ dso-java Main I am servicing requests... Incrementing counter by: 3 Proxy returns: 3 {code}
*Node 2:* {code} $ dso-java Main Proxy returns: 6 (Press Ctrl-c on Node 1) I am servicing requests... (Run Node 3) Incrementing counter by: 3 {code}
*Node 3:* {code} $ dso-java Main Proxy returns: 9 {code}
